About the evaluation:
* The pre-examination questions can be found from the section of the "study materials".
* A student will take a "ticket" containing five questions covering all subjects handled in the course of "Applied electrochemistry" before the start of the written examination.
* Five questions will be selected from the list of the pre-examination questions by the responsible lecturer (Dr. Alar Jänes).
* The answering to the examination questions includes detail explanation and the presentation of the appropriate equations (with the explanation of the symbols used) and the drawing of the figures/schemes when necessary. 
* Each question can give 10 points.
* Maximum number of points obtainable is 50.

Evaluation criteria

When the student has collected:
* <50% of maximum points possible, the grade is: "F";
* 50% ... 60% of maximum points possible, the grade is: "E";
* 61% ... 70% of maximum points possible, the grade is: "D";
* 71% ... 80% of maximum points possible, the grade is: "C";
* 81% ... 90% of maximum points possible, the grade is: "B";
* 91% ... 100% of maximum points possible, the grade is: "A".
